contentrichtext.text: '''LPAC''' may refer to: * [[LaRouche Political Action Committee]], a political action committee comprising part of the Worldwide LaRouche Youth Movement * [[Lesbian Political Action Committee]], a political action committee serving to represent the interests of lesbians in the United States * [[Liberty Political Action Conference]], a political conference held annually by Campaign for Liberty * [[Lincoln Performing Arts Centre]], an auditorium in Lincoln, England * [[London Planning Advisory Committee]], a former organisation of local government in London, England * [[Lossless predictive audio compression]], a lossless audio compression algorithm {{disambig}}
